	<td>
In the first semester of joining BCA, I learnt programming in the basic C language and I made my first own computer program, 'a simple 
Birthday Card'. It was nothing big, but the only fact that I could make a computer do that gave me a great feeling. It took me just
some time to realize that making a computer program or creating something using a computer is just another form of expressing our creativity,
just as an artist does with painting an artwork or an author by writinga a book.
<br><br>
all great things are built in teams, when you collaborate with other people. Whwther you want to make a lot of money or just want to change the world, computer programming is a highly powerful skill.
To be able to come up with an idea and then actually code it to reality and then sharing it with everyone just by press of a few keyboard keys, I think we are the first generation in the world to have had such kind of experience.
<br><br>
Knowing how to use a computer very well, is one of the closest thing we can get to a super power. In BCA at SMC, Shirva we get to learn atleast one programming language each semester.

